The paper deals with the problem of structure learning for Bayesian networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of mathematical models and multivariate regression suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem of structure learning also involves optimization and computational complexity, which could place the paper in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the NP-hardness of the problem, which could suggest a connection to the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the use of binary variables and discrete values suggests a possible connection to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
